    <div id="content_panel"> 
     <div id="column_w610"> 
      <div class="header_01">
       Challenges beyond food security...
      </div> 
      <p>Feeding ever increasing world population to satiety has become the most daunting task of the century in the aftermath of ever increasing demand for food, shrinking the extent of arable lands, decreasing potential food production from natural resources, global warming, pollution, and consequences of human interventions. Hence, food security is of prime concern in most part of the globe for centuries. <br><br> In the process of achieving food security, overwhelming evidences of food borne illnesses and hazards accumulate, raising the unanswered question “Are we consuming safe food?” Ever since these occurrences of food borne illnesses surfaced, attention of the scientific community is evenly, if not more, focused on food safety than food security. Understanding the significance of both of them in the context of “Providing safe food for everybody” the theme of our conference surfaced as “Challenges beyond food security”. <br><br> This conference is therefore focused on one of the most attended areas of the research arena both at national and international context. Researchers, practitioners, policymakers and all other interested personnel around the world are invited to share their findings, knowledge and expertise under this theme.<br><br> Purpose of opening this conference to wide international audience is to bring the knowledge of current and foreseen issues of food security and food safety into a single platform and to share others experiences for “providing safer food for everybody”.</p> 
      <p>&nbsp;</p> 
     </div> 
